165
00:11:59,052 --> 00:12:01,851
- How are you feeling?
- Better.

166
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:07,500
So your daughter wants to be a singer?

167
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:010,300
Yep, since she was 5.

168
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,600
You know, it's not what everyone thinks it is.

169
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:17,500
Once the glam wears off, it's just a
lot of hotel rooms, lots of airports.

170
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:19,500
That's what she wants.

171
00:12:22,784 --> 00:12:25,400
The first number is Gio, my vocal coach.

172
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,600
If he says she can sing, she can sing.

173
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:30,300
He'll give her coaching
she needs, the fee is on me.

174
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,700
The second number is my manager.

175
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,762
If Gio clears her, he'll
make sure she gets a shot.

176
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:41,060
- Thank you.
- No, Mr. Mills, thank you.

177
00:12:57,402 --> 00:12:59,575
- There she is.
- Dad.

178
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,800
- Hi, sweetie.
- Hey.

179
00:13:06,576 --> 00:13:07,500
- Hi.
- Hi.

180
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,300
Don't look so excited.

181
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:12,900
I was just surprised. I thought
it was just gonna be Kim and I.

182
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,600
I asked Mom to come.

183
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:20,500
One raspberry-banana milkshake, extra
cherries, just the way you like it.

184
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,500
- Thanks.
- Lennie... Lenore.

185
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:25,200
- Would you like something?
- I'm fine, thanks.

186
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,226
So?

187
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,800
So, Dad, guess what.

188
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:31,000
- You know my friend Amanda?
- Yep.

189
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:34,800
Her cousins asked us to spend
vacation with them in Paris.

190
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:35,600
How cool is that?

191
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:38,500
- Why do you want to go to Paris?
- Dad. Hello?

192
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,284
The Louvre, the Impressionist
museum, the Picasso Museum.

193
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,800
I didn't know you were so into art.

194
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,538
Are you kidding? I've been to
the MOMA, like, a hundred times.

195
00:13:46,701 --> 00:13:51,457
Amanda went to France last summer and when she
came back she could practically speak French.

196
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,343
And because you're under 18...

197
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:58,345
...you need my permission
to leave the country?

198
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:02,346
Dad, please. I really, really wanna go.

199
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:05,352
They've got this like sick
apartment overlooking the river.

200
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:07,980
- Just you and Amanda?
- And her cousins.

201
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:11,393
Don't make a big deal out of
this, Bryan. Just sign the paper.

202
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:19,499
- What?
- I'm not comfortable with this.

203
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,900
- Dad.
- I know the world, sweetie.

204
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,199
- Dad, please. 
- I don't think a 17-year-old should be travelling alone.

205
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,499
- I'm not gonna be alone.
- Two 17-year-olds.

206
00:14:27,657 --> 00:14:28,659
Amanda's 19.

207
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:37,399
How about this? How about if I go along?

208
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:40,503
You won't know I'm there. I'm
very good at being invisible.

209
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:43,262
As you so amply demonstrated
for most of her life.

210
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:45,017
Just sign the paper, Bryan.

211
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,930
I'll think about it.

212
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,500
Everyone at this table
knows what that means.

213
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:55,736
Hey, Kimmy, there's something else.

214
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,523
- I don't want anything else.
- Kim.

215
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:07,100
- I don't get you.
- What?

216
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,955
You sacrificed our marriage
in the service of the country.

217
00:15:10,118 --> 00:15:12,871
You made a mess of your life
in service of your country.

218
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:16,299
Can't you sacrifice a little
this one time for your own daughter?

219
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:19,919
- I would sacrifice anything for her.
- Then what's your problem?

220
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:22,385
I'm not comfortable
putting my daughter at risk.

221
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:26,555
Putting our daughter at
risk by going to Paris?

222
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:29,012
You're pathetic.

223
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:47,201
- She's coming.
- Thanks.

224
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:51,497
Three conditions.

225
00:15:51,826 --> 00:15:54,500
The address and phone number
of where you're staying.

226
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:57,632
You move, I wanna know where
and with whom you'll be staying.

227
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:01,385
Call me when you land. Call me
every night before you go to sleep.

228
00:16:01,544 --> 00:16:03,296
It's international. My number is in.

229
00:16:03,463 --> 00:16:05,591
- Okay, awesome.
- Kimmy, you're not focused.

230
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:07,053
- I am.
- What did I say?

231
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:10,561
You said call you when I land,
every night before I go to sleep...

232
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:13,564
...your phone's international,
the number's programmed in.

233
00:16:13,723 --> 00:16:16,897
Okay, one last thing. I get
to take you to the airport.

234
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:18,561
Okay.

235
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:21,322
- There you go.
- Yes.

236
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:24,826
Thank you, Daddy. Thank
you, thank you, thank you.

237
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,702
Mom!

238
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:29,785
I love you, Dad.

239
