I need you to be focused.

720
01:04:04,299 --> 01:04:06,176
Are you focused yet?

721
01:04:16,019 --> 01:04:17,191
Where is this girl?

722
01:04:17,812 --> 01:04:19,564
Where is she?

723
01:04:48,093 --> 01:04:51,939
You know, we used to
outsource this kind of thing.

724
01:04:52,097 --> 01:04:54,725
But what we found was the
countries we outsourced to...

725
01:04:54,891 --> 01:04:58,316
...had unreliable power
grids. Very Third World.

726
01:04:58,478 --> 01:05:00,822
You'd turn on a switch,
power wouldn't come on...

727
01:05:00,980 --> 01:05:04,985
...and then tempers would get short.
People would resort to pulling fingernails.

728
01:05:05,151 --> 01:05:07,495
Acid drips on bare skin.

729
01:05:07,654 --> 01:05:10,077
The whole exercise would
become counterproductive.

730
01:05:10,240 --> 01:05:11,913
But here, the power's stable.

731
01:05:12,075 --> 01:05:14,419
Here, there's a nice, even flow.

732
01:05:14,577 --> 01:05:17,877
Here, you can flip a switch
and the power stays on all day.

733
01:05:22,001 --> 01:05:23,344
Where is she?

734
01:05:44,232 --> 01:05:48,203
Now, I don't have any more time
to waste, Marko from Tropoja.

735
01:05:48,653 --> 01:05:50,951
Give me what I need or
this switch'll stay on...

736
01:05:51,114 --> 01:05:54,118
...till they turn power off
for lack of payment on the bill.

737
01:05:55,368 --> 01:05:56,620
Where is my daughter?

738
01:05:57,162 --> 01:06:00,632
We don't keep virgins, we sell them.

739
01:06:00,832 --> 01:06:03,005
She was virgin, lot of money.

740
01:06:03,168 --> 01:06:05,341
You sold my daughter? You sold her?

741
01:06:07,338 --> 01:06:08,965
To who?

742
01:06:09,674 --> 01:06:11,301
I don't know.

743
01:06:13,761 --> 01:06:15,638
- What? -
Saint-Clair.

744
01:06:16,139 --> 01:06:17,186
Saint-Clair.

745
01:06:17,599 --> 01:06:20,193
Saint-Clair? Saint-Clair.
Is that a person, a place?

746
01:06:21,769 --> 01:06:24,818
Person. Patrice Saint-Clair.

747
01:06:24,981 --> 01:06:26,028
Patrice Saint-Clair.

748
01:06:27,192 --> 01:06:28,535
Where can I find him?

749
01:06:29,486 --> 01:06:31,329
I don't know, I don't know.

750
01:06:32,113 --> 01:06:34,832
I don't know. I don't
know. I don't know.

751
01:06:35,033 --> 01:06:37,286
Please! I don't know!

752
01:06:37,452 --> 01:06:41,457
I don't know! No! Please! Please.

753
01:06:41,623 --> 01:06:43,466
Please.

754
01:06:43,625 --> 01:06:45,753
Not that. Please.

755
01:06:45,919 --> 01:06:47,296
I believe you.

756
01:06:50,131 --> 01:06:52,475
But it's not gonna save you.

757
01:07:06,856 --> 01:07:09,279
- I'm home.
- Daddy!

758
01:07:09,442 --> 01:07:11,740
- Hello, darlings.
- Hi, Dad.

759
01:07:13,196 --> 01:07:15,415
The chicken smells great.

760
01:07:15,573 --> 01:07:17,450
Look who dropped by.

761
01:07:18,243 --> 01:07:20,837
Bryan, what a pleasant surprise.

762
01:07:21,037 --> 01:07:22,084
Jean-Claude.

763
01:07:22,247 --> 01:07:24,716
The children waited up for you.

764
01:07:24,874 --> 01:07:28,219
If you tuck them in, maybe we can
eat before everything gets cold.

765
01:07:28,378 --> 01:07:29,925
Bryan, will you do the honors?

766
01:07:30,129 --> 01:07:32,006
<i>- Sure.
- I'll be just a minute.</i>

767
01:07:32,173 --> 01:07:33,675
Children, bedtime.

768
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:34,888
Yes, it is.

769
01:07:35,051 --> 01:07:37,099
It's late. Get to bed now.

770
01:07:43,101 --> 01:07:44,193
Sleep well.

771
01:08:02,537 --> 01:08:04,710
I was just telling Bryan
how nice it's been...

772
01:08:04,872 --> 01:08:07,045
...since you left the
old job for the new one.

773
01:08:07,208 --> 01:08:10,052
Home every night for dinner,
get to see the kids more.

774
01:08:10,211 --> 01:08:13,306
Yeah, must be nice coming home
every night, seeing your kids.

775
01:08:13,506 --> 01:08:15,600
Bryan has been thinking
about relocating.

776
01:08:16,009 --> 01:08:17,477
Really? Yes.

777
01:08:17,635 --> 01:08:19,433
To Paris, he's been visiting houses.

778
01:08:19,596 --> 01:08:22,270
- White or dark meat?
- Dark, please.

779
01:08:22,432 --> 01:08:23,775
Find anything interesting?

780
01:08:23,933 --> 01:08:27,733
As a matter of fact, I did, in the
10th arrondissement on Rue Paradis.

781
01:08:28,646 --> 01:08:31,149
People there know someone
that works in your office.

782
01:08:31,357 --> 01:08:33,359
A Mr. Macon. Do you know him?

783
01:08:33,526 --> 01:08:35,779
Oh, Henry. I call him Mr. Nervous.

784
01:08:35,945 --> 01:08:39,666
Always seems like he's about
to have a problem. Carrots?

785
01:08:39,824 --> 01:08:41,667
I got to the bottom of it, Jean-Claude.

786
01:08:41,993 --> 01:08:43,165
I know everything.

787
01:08:43,870 --> 01:08:46,168
I hope you're not involved in this shit.

788
01:08:47,498 --> 01:08:50,377
- What shit?
- This is not the time or place, Bryan.

789
01:08:50,543 --> 01:08:52,637
Are you involved? Involved in what?

790
01:08:53,254 --> 01:08:54,756
What are you two talking about?

791
01:08:54,922 --> 01:08:58,552
- Are you?
- My salary is X, my expenses are Y.

792
01:08:58,718 --> 01:09:00,766
As long as my family is provided for...

793
01:09:00,928 --> 01:09:03,556
...I do not care where
the difference comes from.

794
01:09:03,723 --> 01:09:05,600
That is my entire involvement.

795
01:09:05,767 --> 01:09:07,769
- What about my family?
- I told you...

796
01:09:07,935 --> 01:09:10,404
...I would help as long
as it didn't cause trouble.

797
01:09:10,563 --> 01:09:11,906
Who is Patrice Saint-Clair?

798
01:09:12,065 --> 01:09:15,569
I don't know, I don't care. I
am driving you to the airport.

799
01:09:15,777 --> 01:09:17,029
Jean-Claude.

800
01:09:17,195 --> 01:09:18,321
Shut up, Isabelle. Shut up!

801
01:09:18,488 --> 01:09:20,161
Let's get going. Dinner is over.

802
01:09:20,323 --> 01:09:22,121
- I'm not finished yet.
- Yes, you are.

803
01:09:22,367 --> 01:09:25,246
- No!
- No, I'm not.

804
01:09:29,957 --> 01:09:33,211
That's what happens when you sit
behind a desk. You forget things.

805
01:09:33,378 --> 01:09:35,847
Like the weight in the
hand of a gun that's loaded.

806
01:09:37,924 --> 01:09:38,971
Isabelle!

807
01:09:39,133 --> 01:09:40,305
You asshole!

808
01:09:40,510 --> 01:09:41,682
It's a flesh wound.

809
01:09:41,844 --> 01:09:45,565
But if you don't get me what I
need, the last thing you'll see...

810
01:09:45,723 --> 01:09:47,725
...is the bullet I put between her eyes.

811
01:09:47,892 --> 01:09:50,941
Now, Patrice Saint-Clair.

812
01:10:02,407 --> 01:10:04,375
You could've made this less painful...

813
01:10:04,534 --> 01:10:08,664
...if you had been more concerned about
my daughter and less about your desk.

814
01:10:08,830 --> 01:10:11,174
Please apologize to your wife for me.

815
01:11:16,439 --> 01:11:19,318
- Can I help you? - Yes, I'm
here to see Mr. Saint-Clair.

816
01:11:19,484 --> 01:11:21,031
Your name, please.

817
01:11:25,031 --> 01:11:26,954
I'm sorry, your name is not on the list.

818
01:11:27,116 --> 01:11:28,709
Oh, please check again.

819
01:11:31,746 --> 01:11:33,464
Inside.

820
01:12:21,087 --> 01:12:22,339
May I help you, sir?

821
01:12:27,969 --> 01:12:30,472
- Your champagne.
- Yeah, I will take it.

822
01:12:40,273 --> 01:12:43,527
<i>I have 50,000. Fifty thousand.</i>

823
01:12:45,319 --> 01:12:47,367
<i>Fifty thousand.</i>

824
01:12:48,906 --> 01:12:52,160
<i>One hundred, 100,000.</i>

825
01:12:53,995 --> 01:12:57,169
<i>One hundred, 150.</i>

826
01:12:58,291 --> 01:12:59,463
<i>I have 150.</i>

827
01:13:00,084 --> 01:13:02,257
Your champagne, sir.

828
01:13:03,004 --> 01:13:05,723
<i>Two, I have two, 250.</i>

829
01:13:05,882 --> 01:13:06,929
May I serve?

830
01:13:07,091 --> 01:13:08,468
- Please.
- I have 250.

831
01:13:10,303 --> 01:13:12,021
<i>Two-fifty.</i>

832
01:13:12,597 --> 01:13:15,646
<i>Sold for 250,000.</i>

833
01:13:33,701 --> 01:13:35,874
<i>The last item.</i>

834
01:13:36,203 --> 01:13:38,706
<i>As usual, we save the best for last.</i>

835
01:13:39,040 --> 01:13:41,213
<i>Speaks English, some French.</i>

836
01:13:41,375 --> 01:13:42,843
<i>Certified pure.</i>

837
01:13:52,762 --> 01:13:53,809
- Sorry.
- Get out.

838
01:13:55,389 --> 01:13:58,142
<i>The bidding will begin at 100,000.</i>

839
01:14:01,604 --> 01:14:03,732
<i>One hundred.</i>

840
01:14:13,658 --> 01:14:15,456
<i>One hundred thousand.</i>

841
01:14:15,660 --> 01:14:17,833
- I said...
- I heard what you said.

842
01:14:17,995 --> 01:14:19,338
Buy her.

843
01:14:19,538 --> 01:14:20,630
<i>I have 100.</i>

844
01:14:22,375 --> 01:14:25,128
<i>- Buy her.
- One-fifty.</i>

845
01:14:25,336 --> 01:14:26,883
<i>Two hundred.</i>

846
01:14:27,588 --> 01:14:30,262
<i>Two-fifty, three, 350.</i>

847
01:14:30,466 --> 01:14:33,720
<i>Three hundred and fifty thousand.</i>

848
01:14:34,345 --> 01:14:36,564
<i>Four. Four.</i>

849
01:14:37,056 --> 01:14:39,525
<i>Four-fifty, 450.</i>

850
01:14:39,725 --> 01:14:41,602
<i>Four hundred and fifty thousand.</i>

851
01:14:42,311 --> 01:14:43,403
<i>Four-fifty.</i>

852
01:14:44,563 --> 01:14:46,531
<i>Five hundred. Five hundred thousand.</i>

853
01:14:46,691 --> 01:14:50,696
<i>Five hundred thousand. Sold.</i>

854
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:54,874
<i>That concludes the sales for
tonight. Thank you all for coming.</i>

855
01:14:55,324 --> 01:14:58,294
<i>- You can collect your purchases directly.
- Move.</i>

856
01:14:58,452 --> 01:15:02,502
- You will never get away with this.
- If you wanna live, you'll make sure I do.

857
01:15:12,299 --> 01:15:14,768
Now, Mr...?

858
01:15:20,975 --> 01:15:24,445
Well, we know you're not this
man. So, what do we call you?

859
01:15:27,732 --> 01:15:29,655
It doesn't matter what we call you...

860
01:15:29,817 --> 01:15:32,286
...what does matter is
what you're doing here.

861
01:15:33,654 --> 01:15:35,622
The last girl, I'm her father.

862
01:15:38,159 --> 01:15:41,288
- Oh, my.
- Give her to me.

863
01:15:42,621 --> 01:15:44,874
I wish I could, honestly.

864
01:15:45,041 --> 01:15:46,759
See, I'm a father myself.

865
01:15:46,917 --> 01:15:48,965
I have two sons and a daughter...

866
01:15:49,128 --> 01:15:52,132
...but let me tell you
something, Mr. Whoever-You-Are.

867
01:15:52,298 --> 01:15:53,641
This is a business.

868
01:15:53,799 --> 01:15:55,551
This is a very unique business...

869
01:15:55,718 --> 01:15:58,471
<i>...with a very unique clientele.
- I'll pay.</i>

870
01:15:58,679 --> 01:16:01,148
In this business, you
have no refunds, returns...

871
01:16:01,307 --> 01:16:03,401
...discounts, buybacks.
All sales are final.

872
01:16:03,559 --> 01:16:08,440
Besides discretion, it's
about the only rule we have.

873
01:16:10,357 --> 01:16:12,860
Kill him. Quietly. I have guests.

874
01:17:11,085 --> 01:17:13,463
Would you please go see
which part of "quietly"...

875
01:17:13,629 --> 01:17:16,303
- ... they did not understand?
- Yes, sir.

876
01:17:35,568 --> 01:17:39,289
Okay, we can resolve
this. I know how you feel.

877
01:17:39,446 --> 01:17:42,120
We should talk, okay?
We can work this out.

878
01:17:44,410 --> 01:17:46,128
You have no idea...

879
01:17:47,246 --> 01:17:48,463
- Where is she?
- Please.

880
01:17:48,664 --> 01:17:49,916
Understand. Please try...

881
01:17:54,628 --> 01:17:57,723
There's a boat by the quay.

882
01:17:58,924 --> 01:18:00,426
Please understand.

883
01:18:00,593 --> 01:18:04,939
It was all business, it wasn't personal.

884
01:18:05,139 --> 01:18:06,891
It was all personal to me.

885
01:20:53,057 --> 01:20:54,855
They are being prepared, sir.

886
01:21:56,245 --> 01:21:58,498
You! Take the girls to the Sheik.

887
01:21:59,248 --> 01:22:00,374
You! Come with me.

888
01:22:01,083 --> 01:22:02,630
We have an intruder.

889
01:22:02,835 --> 01:22:04,052
<i>Search the boat.</i>

890
01:22:04,628 --> 01:22:07,347
<i>Kill him if necessary.</i>

891
01:23:12,988 --> 01:23:14,410
It's safer in your room, Excellence.

892
01:23:14,865 --> 01:23:16,663
What's going on? Who is it?

893
01:23:16,825 --> 01:23:18,919
The girl's father. He wants her back.

894
01:23:19,203 --> 01:23:20,876
I'll get rid of the dog.

895
01:25:03,932 --> 01:25:05,024
We can ne...

896
01:25:16,987 --> 01:25:20,708
- Daddy.
- Kim.

897
01:25:21,450 --> 01:25:23,623
You came for me.

898
01:25:28,165 --> 01:25:29,633
You came for me.

899
01:25:32,377 --> 01:25:34,471
I told you I would.

900
01:26:02,366 --> 01:26:04,744
<i>May I have your attention.</i>

901
01:26:04,910 --> 01:26:06,583
<i>If you're waiting for oversized bags...</i>

902
01:26:08,080 --> 01:26:09,957
Mom.

903
01:26:11,708 --> 01:26:13,676
Oh, my God.

904
01:26:14,086 --> 01:26:16,339
Oh, sweetie.

905
01:26:17,005 --> 01:26:19,349
Oh, here, let me get that for you.

906
01:26:19,508 --> 01:26:21,431
Bryan, if there's anything you need...

907
01:26:22,803 --> 01:26:24,976
I've got everything I need.

908
01:26:25,138 --> 01:26:27,766
I love you so much.

909
01:26:29,893 --> 01:26:31,987
Stuart.

910
01:26:32,896 --> 01:26:34,898
Thank you.

911
01:26:42,155 --> 01:26:45,125
<i>Attention, travelers.
You are not required to...</i>

912
01:26:45,283 --> 01:26:47,206
Shall we go?

913
01:26:52,249 --> 01:26:54,718
Sure you don't wanna ride with us?

914
01:26:55,335 --> 01:26:57,713
I'll be fine. I'll take a cab. Thanks.

915
01:26:57,879 --> 01:26:59,973
All right.

916
01:27:08,306 --> 01:27:10,479
- I love you, Dad.
- Love you too.

917
01:27:33,623 --> 01:27:36,593
- Where are we?
- I told you. It's a surprise.

918
01:27:38,545 --> 01:27:40,513
Hi. Hi.

919
01:27:43,550 --> 01:27:46,929
When someone says "hi," it's
usually polite to say "hi" back.

920
01:27:47,679 --> 01:27:48,771
Hi.

921
01:27:48,930 --> 01:27:50,398
I heard you wanna be a singer.

922
01:27:50,557 --> 01:27:52,355
- I do.
- She does.

923
01:27:53,935 --> 01:27:57,280
Well, come on in.
Let's see what you got.

